      "body": "> This might be a better mailing list or delvingbitcoin post. I think the bip32 ambiguity is solved in bitcoin core by using descriptors which are precise and explicit about derivation path.\n\n You are right that this may not the ideal place to discuss this. I wasn't sure where to share this. Thanks for the tip.\n\n> Also bitcoin core does use 'h' for hardened indexes:\n> https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/26076\n\nInteresting! I used the [ParseHDKeypath](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/util/bip32.cpp#L15) function for testing. As mentioned:\n> Results concern only the path parsing API.\n\nIt seems to not include `h` support. I see there was an attempt to add it in [#28192](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/28192) though that was scratched because [#22341](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/22341) was closed.\n",
